First of all, rangers can tank...in limited situations.  With cleric shammy buffs I easily have over 1000 ac and 3500 hps at 55, which while not that impressive compared to warriors is sufficient to get the job done in places like velk's or easier seb camps.  I have tanked frenzy in velk's, disco, and chef.  Is it the most efficient way to get things done?  Heck no, I am always happy in those situations to see a warrior join the group.  But in a pinch it can be done<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
However tanking is obviously not our primary skill.  We are excellent, however, at damage dealing and aggro control (and with jolt/root ability we can do that damage without having to periodically flop on the ground<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ).  The part I enjoy most is controlling aggro.  Mob beating the snot out of the chanter/shammy etc.?  Flame lick/flame lick, wait a few seconds then jolt or root and back off.  Of course on raid level mobs the chances are you won't last long, but it's worth it if you just kept a critically needed person alive.  In normal exp groups root is also a great mez breaking tool, as hopefully by the time it wears off the mob will be glued to the tanks rather than make a beeline for the chanter as sometimes seems to happen with a warrior breaking mez.  <br>
This is not even mentioning trueshot, weaponshield, coe/strength of nature/predator/chloro buffs, tracking, etc. that others have brought up.  I don't feel I need ports, or quite frankly any other additional abilities in order to be a contributing member of an exp group or raid.  Not to mention it's bad enough being bugged for ports while playing my druid, double the port requests and I'd probably have to go on some deranged rampage<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
