<br>
    As a human ranger I've heard all the lowbrow, inept &quot;Anti Ranger&quot; comments you could imagine.  All the top rangers I know can easily handle themselves in groups as well as Raid situations.  Now while I'm not yer average equipped ranger ( 1400 ac 3K hps 1400+ atk self)  I'm not the top equipped ranger either.  And in most situations I can handle tanking for groups, and sure as hell carry my damage output weight on Raids.<br>
<br>
While there was a time when it was a heavy burden to allow any hybrid into yer exp group ( remember 40% exp penalty? eppp).  And many of us leveled up while bearing it, I assure you that having a hybrid ( played well of course) in your group is a good thing.  Think Flexibility and you'll enjoy the game more, endure the mindset that you have to have certain combos in your group before you'll do well and perhaps Tic Tac toe is more your game.  I just love minds that are so inflexible they miss out on real fun ;P  <br>
<br>
As someone so wisely said early, there is no awful/perfect classes.  Just play what you wish to play <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
